---
import ArticleLayout from "@/layouts/ArticleLayout.astro";
---

<ArticleLayout
  title="Architecture"
  description="The current architecture view for Articulate, limited to what has been established so far."
  eyebrow="Current state"
>
  <p>
    This section describes the current state of the system, not the full history of how it arrived
    here. At this stage, Articulate has established its purpose, principles, and documentation model.
    Detailed runtime architecture will be added only when decisions and implementation evidence exist.
  </p>

  <div class="callout">
    <h2>Current Architectural Position</h2>
    <p>
      Articulate is being established as a production-oriented reference architecture and public
      architectural journal. The repository is the canonical record; the website is the navigable
      narrative surface.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2>Future Views</h2>
  <div class="route-grid">
    {[
      "System context",
      "Capability architecture",
      "Conversational architecture",
      "Runtime architecture",
      "Data and memory architecture",
      "Workflow and agent architecture",
      "Security and governance",
      "Operations and observability"
    ].map((view) => (
      <article class="index-card">
        <h3>{view}</h3>
        <p>This view will be added when the architecture has enough evidence to describe it responsibly.</p>
      </article>
    ))}
  </div>
</ArticleLayout>
